1
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,880
{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

2
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,880
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第四季  第五集

3
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:02,880
两个月前  卢卡斯·古德温被从印第安纳州
Lucas Goodwin was released from a federal detention center

4
00:03:01,210 --> 00:03:10,570
{\an8}卢卡斯·古德温的家

5
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:05,420
泰瑞豪特一家联邦监狱释放
in Terre Haute, Indiana, two months ago.

6
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:08,650
联调局调查员搜查了他在俄亥俄州代顿的
FBI investigators searched his witness protection residence

7
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:10,810
-证人保护计划住处  -他怎么会被释放
- in Dayton, Ohio... - Why was he even out of jail?

8
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:13,550
他在一起调查中协助了司法部
He helped the DOJ with an ongoing investigation.

9
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:14,860
你怎么会不知道
How did you not know that?

10
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:18,420
证人保护计划  出于安全考虑高度保密
WITSEC. Only need-to-know for security reasons.

11
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,470
我们今天在他家发现了这个
We found this today at his house. 

12
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,140
大概是遗书吧
A suicide note, I guess.

13
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:30,910
{\an8}...外遇...佐伊·巴恩斯

14
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:39,110
这不能被公开
This can't go public.

15
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,960
我们还没对媒体透露半句
We haven't told the press anything. 

16
00:03:41,210 --> 00:03:42,780
但这是证据
But this is evidence.

17
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:44,660
一旦报告出来
Once the report comes out...

18
00:03:44,290 --> 00:03:46,140
{\an8}道格·斯坦普  幕僚长

19
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:50,300
{\an8}瑞秋·波斯纳

20
00:04:01,130 --> 00:04:02,450
把这个电邮给我
Email this to me.

21
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,390
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood?

22
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,720
现在凌晨两点了  您要回家吗
It's two o'clock in the morning. Would you like to go home?

23
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:19,860
嗯  我待会儿就出去
Oh, yes, I'll be out in a moment.

24
00:04:19,910 --> 00:04:20,980
是  夫人
Yes, ma'am.

25
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:01,290
他的肝再生速度不够快
His liver is just not regenerating fast enough.

26
00:05:01,290 --> 00:05:03,020
那具体是什么意思
What does that mean, exactly?

27
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,830
他需要移植  否则会死
He needs a transplant, or he'll die.

28
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,400
-什么时候  -几天之内
- How soon? - Days.

29
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,510
我们将他列为了1号情况
We've made him Status 1.

30
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:14,780
我们相信能为他找到合适的肝脏
I'm optimistic we'll find him a suitable liver.

31
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:16,650
接受者名单是机密
The recipient list is classified.

32
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,620
只有您两位政府成员
You're the only two members of the administration

33
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:19,450
知情
who've been briefed.

34
00:05:19,450 --> 00:05:20,730
第一夫人知道了吗
Is the First Lady aware? 

35
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:23,160
是的  我今天下午告诉她了
Yes, I informed her this afternoon.

36
00:05:31,010 --> 00:05:32,170
我可以进来吗
May I?

37
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,930
请吧
Please.

38
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:37,210
我知道很晚了  但他们说你没睡
I know it's late, but they said you were up, so...

39
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:39,200
我知道  我就是一天都没吃东西了
No, I know. I just hadn't eaten all day.

40
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,570
你也是吧
I'm sure you haven't.

41
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:44,170
-来点沙拉吗  -好啊  谢谢
- Would you like some salad? - Sure. Thank you.

42
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,930
弗兰克的事  真是可怕
It's scary, about Frank.

43
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,450
弗兰西斯是个斗士
Well, Francis is a fighter.

44
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:57,180
真希望我能问他的建议
I wish I could ask his advice.

45
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:59,660
我明早要跟佩特罗夫通电话了
I have my call with Petrov in the morning.

46
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:07,620
我对计划颇为了解  这点我有自信
I feel good about my understanding of the plan.

47
00:06:08,550 --> 00:06:12,210
我担心的是他在电话里威胁我
My concern is him railroading me on the call.

48
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:14,030
你希望我跟你一起打吗
Well, would you like me to be on it? 

49
00:06:14,030 --> 00:06:15,640
多个人听听
An extra set of ears.

50
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:20,040
我不知道凯茜会有什么想法
I don't... I don't know how Cathy would feel about that.

51
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,910
不非得让她知道啊
Well, she doesn't need to know.

52
00:06:23,910 --> 00:06:26,620
我可以在这里听
I could just listen from up here.

53
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,060
如果你有麻烦  或许我可以发点建议过去
And maybe I could type a note if you get into trouble.

54
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:49,740
...对总统的恢复闭口不言
...tight-lipped on the president's recovery.

55
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:52,800
到目前  据报他情况稳定
As of now, he's reported to be in stable condition.

56
00:06:52,810 --> 00:06:55,210
尚无媒体被允许进入医院
No press has been allowed into the hospital.

57
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:57,780
共和党候选人威尔·康威
Republican presidential hopeful Will Conway

58
00:06:57,780 --> 00:07:00,780
今早在亚利桑那州一场集会上提到了总统
spoke of the president at a rally in Arizona this morning.

59
00:07:00,780 --> 00:07:02,800
我经常批评安德伍德总统
I've criticized President Underwood often.

60
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,660
但此刻  他是我们的总统
But right now, he's our president...

61
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,370
明天来吧  我们没油了
Come back tomorrow. We're all out.

62
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,190
{\an8}两党要团结一致
...and we have to pull together, both sides of the aisle...

63
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,050
我们今天没油了
We're all out for today. 

64
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,060
抱歉  明天再来吧
Sorry, come back tomorrow.

65
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:11,940
-没油了  没油了  -不是吧
- We're all out, guys. We're all out. - Are you serious?

66
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:13,650
明天再来吧  我们今天没油了  先生
Come back tomorrow. We're all out for today, sir.

67
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:15,110
真扯
Bullshit!

68
00:07:24,050 --> 00:07:25,800
我能从你这儿吸几加仑吗
Can I siphon a couple of gallons from you?

69
00:07:26,890 --> 00:07:28,680
五十块  我没油了已经
Fifty bucks. I'm running on fumes.

70
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,330
我还得送孩子上学  送老公上班
I gotta get my kids to school, and my husband to work--

71
00:07:30,330 --> 00:07:31,930
八十块  两加仑
Eighty bucks, two gallons.

72
00:07:31,930 --> 00:07:34,000
抱歉  帮不了你  抱歉
Sorry, I can't help you. Sorry.

73
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:37,060
{\an8}普通汽油  高级汽油  精品汽油  全部现金支付

74
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:52,770
{\an7}杰·夏普  你在华府吗  这边加班加点呢

75
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:54,840
{\an7}总统  油价危机

76
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:57,260
{\an7}如果能休息一下就太好了

77
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:01,680
{\an8}雷·丹顿  佛罗里达呢  看爸妈来了

78
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:04,980
{\an7}或许也好  诱惑最讨厌了

79
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:12,020
{\an8}我想你...

80
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:27,350
接通了吗
The line's open? 

81
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:29,350
莫斯科就等您了  先生
Moscow is ready when you are, sir.

82
00:08:33,210 --> 00:08:35,180
放在这里就好
You can set it up here.

83
00:08:40,210 --> 00:08:41,570
我的小抄
My Cliff Notes.

84
00:08:47,910 --> 00:08:49,100
我准备好了
I'm ready.

85
00:08:49,950 --> 00:08:51,490
{\an8}说话别含糊其辞

86
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:57,910
{\an8}自信  你有筹码的

87
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,210
总统先生  您已与佩特罗夫总统接通
Mr. President, you're on with President Petrov.

88
00:09:01,210 --> 00:09:02,350
总统先生
Mr. President.

89
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:05,210
俄国举国上下都在为总统的康复祈祷
All of Russia is praying for the president's recovery.

90
00:09:05,210 --> 00:09:07,950
希望代我转达对安德伍德夫人的问候
I hope you will extend my warm thoughts to Mrs. Underwood.

91
00:09:07,950 --> 00:09:09,150
我会的
I certainly will.

92
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,920
你真是勇敢
You're a brave man 

93
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,680
在如此艰难的时刻接手
to take over during such difficult times.

94
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,430
我只想确保
I just want to make sure

95
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:16,830
我们找到可行方案解决这场油价...
we find a manageable resolution to this oil--

96
00:09:16,830 --> 00:09:19,330
我读过你写的一些书  总统先生
I've read some of your books, Mr. President.

97
00:09:19,530 --> 00:09:22,910
我刚读完《学会学习》
I just finished Learning to Learn. 

98
00:09:23,090 --> 00:09:24,150
很不错
It was good.

99
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:25,210
谢谢
Thank you.

100
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:29,070
有一章关于想象的令我很感兴趣
There was a chapter on visualization that really interested me.

101
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:32,060
是的  是学生可用的工具  帮助他们
Yes, it's a... A tool for students. It helps them--

102
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:35,460
我想请你想象一下
I would like you to visualize something.

103
00:09:36,620 --> 00:09:39,340
你站在苔原上
Now, you're standing in the tundra.

104
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:41,980
大风  暴雪
Um, wind, snow...

105
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:45,090
机器在钻透冰层
machines drilling through the ice,

106
00:09:45,090 --> 00:09:48,690
长长的管线延伸至远处的地平线  你能想象吗
long pipelines stretching to the horizon. Do you see?

107
00:09:48,690 --> 00:09:51,450
如果你想谈西伯利亚  我很乐意...
If you want to talk about Siberia, I'm more than happy to--

108
00:09:51,460 --> 00:09:54,690
不不  你不是在想象
No, no, no. You're not visualizing, 

109
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,300
副总统先生
Mr. Vice President.

110
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,810
闭上你的眼睛
Close your eyes.

111
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,970
{\an8}配合他  让他说

112
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:10,090
好吧  闭上了
All right. They're closed.

113
00:10:10,090 --> 00:10:11,830
很好  那么
Good. Now...

114
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:14,430
想象工人
picture the men 

115
00:10:14,430 --> 00:10:17,580
在钻井和管线上工作
working those drills and pipelines.

116
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,380
他们什么样
What do they look like?

117
00:10:20,650 --> 00:10:23,370
大棉衣  戴手套  穿着靴子
Um, heavy coats, gloves, boots.

118
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:27,600
他们是  中国人吗
Are they... Chinese?

119
00:10:30,370 --> 00:10:33,860
瞧  当我想象的时候
You see, when I picture this, 

120
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:36,020
我看不到中国人
I don't see Chinese.

121
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,900
我同意  中国的控制权越少越好
I agree with you. The less control the Chinese have, the better.

122
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,130
那你为什么把米尔金送去中国
Then why did you send Milkin to China?

123
00:10:41,130 --> 00:10:42,900
你不肯跟我们谈判
You weren't negotiating with us.

124
00:10:42,990 --> 00:10:44,120
我们觉得或许他们的运气会更好
We thought they might have more luck.

125
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:46,720
他们的要求会让我们陷入比之前更糟的境地
Their demands would leave us worse off than we were before.

126
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,830
我可以让国际货币基金组织拿出一半的救市资金
I can get the IMF to provide half the bailout.

127
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:51,230
这可以制衡中国对开采权的要求
This would counteract the Chinese demands for drilling rights--

128
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:53,690
你是想挑拨我们
You are playing us off each other. 

129
00:10:53,690 --> 00:10:54,840
总统先生
Mr. President--

130
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:58,800
我觉得  你是自不量力了  布莱斯先生
I think you're in over your head, Mr. Blythe.

131
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,320
容我解释一下
If you would just give me a chance to elaborate--

132
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,520
凭什么让你解释
Why give you a chance?

133
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:04,090
你对俄国  对中国有什么了解
What do you know about Russia? About China?

134
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,220
我已经听过了...
I've been briefed on--

135
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:07,610
抱歉  但是
Forgive me, but, uh...

136
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,220
我不愿跟
I don't feel comfortable

137
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:13,470
总统以外的人进行谈判
negotiating with anyone other than the president.

138
00:11:13,620 --> 00:11:16,800
等他康复  或许我们可以谈谈
When he recovers, perhaps he and I can speak.

139
00:11:16,130 --> 00:11:17,380
{\an8}告诉他总统可能会死

140
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,960
我们完事了吗
So, are we finished?

141
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,350
{\an8}告诉他总统可能会死

142
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:26,860
总统情况很糟
The president's in very bad shape.

143
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:27,890
先生
Sir...

144
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,770
多严重
How serious is it?

145
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:35,060
{\an8}他得习惯跟你商议

146
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:38,030
他需要肝脏移植
He needs a liver transplant.

147
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,660
我不知道
I wasn't aware that...

148
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:45,780
你最好习惯跟我磋商
You better get used to negotiating with me.

149
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:49,180
如果总统死了  那就是你和我
If the president dies, it's you and I...

150
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:50,890
否则没得可谈
or nothing at all.

151
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:55,340
抱歉  总统先生
My apologies, Mr. President. 

152
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:58,690
我无意侮辱你
I didn't intend to insult you.

153
00:11:58,690 --> 00:12:01,120
我们继续协商  我只求这个
Let's keep a dialogue open. That's all I'm asking.

154
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:04,250
我想给你一份应对中方要求的
I'd like the opportunity to present you with a detailed proposal

155
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,750
具体提议
countering the Chinese demands.

156
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:08,630
我会让国务卿杜兰特跟你的外交部长接洽
I'll have Secretary Durant work with your foreign minister,

157
00:12:08,630 --> 00:12:10,180
然后我们再谈
and then we'll take it from there.

158
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:12,440
这样可以吗
Are you open to that?

159
00:12:13,610 --> 00:12:14,760
当然
Of course.

160
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:19,130
我很期待看到你的提议
I look forward to reviewing your proposal.

161
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,800
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President. 

162
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:23,910
先生  这消息我们还不希望被透露出去
Sir, we didn't want that to get out to the press yet.

163
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,530
美国人民反正也该知道
The American people deserve to know, anyway.

164
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:27,610
先生  俄国人是见软就欺
Sir, the Russians don't respond well to weakness.

165
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,180
现在他们知道总统...
Now that they know that the president--

166
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:31,390
你听到他说愿意协商了
You heard him say he's open to negotiation.

167
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,480
我认为这是进展
I'd say that's progress.

168
00:12:46,050 --> 00:12:47,640
四天了  还没有吗
Four days and still nothing? 

169
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,540
没有记者招待会  没有通报
No press conference, no briefing.

170
00:12:49,540 --> 00:12:50,420
我们得让他们
We have to let them conduct

171
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:52,840
按自己的步调进行调查
their investigation on their own terms.

172
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,470
感觉好像我们被蒙在鼓里
Feels like we're being shut out. 

173
00:12:54,470 --> 00:12:55,510
不仅仅是联调局
This isn't just the bureau.

174
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:56,830
他们还得跟国土安全部协调
They have to coordinate with Homeland

175
00:12:56,830 --> 00:12:59,290
-确保敏感...  -扯淡
- and make sure nothing sensitive-- - That's bullshit.

176
00:12:59,290 --> 00:13:01,450
古德温有什么情况你不希望我们知道
There's something about Goodwin that you don't want us to know.

177
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:02,350
不对
Wrong.

178
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,030
我跟你一样想知道他这么做的动机
I wanna know why he did this just as much as you do...

179
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:07,370
但我们得让联调局做他们的工作
But we've gotta let the FBI do its job.

180
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:23,110
跟我去看他时是同一个论调
Same theory as when I visited him.

181
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,650
那是他达成认罪协议之前  是吗
And that was before he struck the plea, correct?

182
00:13:25,730 --> 00:13:27,370
我鼓励他认罪的
I encouraged him to plead guilty.

183
00:13:27,370 --> 00:13:29,650
他的宣称毫无依据
His claims were unsubstantiated.

184
00:13:29,650 --> 00:13:31,040
跟我们说说你去见古德温之前
Tell us about your meeting with the president

185
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,650
跟总统的见面
prior to that meeting with Goodwin.

186
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,790
卢卡斯拜托我调查  我就调查了
Lucas asked me to investigate. I did.

187
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:38,290
因此采访了安德伍德
That involved an interview with Underwood.

188
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:39,660
你还留着笔记吗
You still have your notes?

189
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:42,340
没有搜查令我不会交出笔记
No notes without a warrant.

190
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:50,750
媒体  没日没夜地打
The press. Calling non-stop. 

191
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,500
我们建议调查期间你不要跟任何人...
We suggest you don't speak to anyone while we're still--

192
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:55,420
别担心  我完全不想被扯进来
Don't worry. I don't have any interest in getting dragged into this.

193
00:13:56,830 --> 00:13:58,540
我去把笔记找出来
Let me go dig up those notes.

194
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:35,790
布莱斯  他告诉佩特罗夫总统需要移植
Blythe... He told Petrov the president needs a transplant.

195
00:14:36,340 --> 00:14:37,700
他为什么要那么做
Why would he do that? 

196
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:39,290
佩特罗夫把他气到了
Petrov got under his skin.

197
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,030
这就是为什么我们本该按你丈夫的计划来
This is why we should've carried out your husband's plan.

198
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,460
我们给了莫斯科太多操作的空间
We're giving Moscow too much room to maneuver--

199
00:14:43,460 --> 00:14:46,420
我们别谈论无法改变的事了  道格
Let's not debate what we can't change, Doug.

200
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:50,170
如果莫斯科知道了  我们就得通知媒体
If Moscow knows, we'll have to notify the press.

201
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:51,900
我们明天就说
We're doing that tomorrow. 

202
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:53,940
由萨克逊医生来做通告
Dr. Saxon will do the briefing.

203
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:55,960
不  我来吧
No, I'll do it. 

204
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,870
还是由第一夫人来说的好
It's better coming from the First Lady.

205
00:15:00,170 --> 00:15:01,210
我同意
I agree.

206
00:15:02,930 --> 00:15:04,630
这事我们也得应对一下
We need to address this, too.

207
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:08,100
联调局在古德温家找到了他的遗书
The FBI found Goodwin's notes in his house.

208
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,800
可以给处理掉吗
Can we make them disappear? 

209
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,240
不行  已经被收为证据了
No, it's already been catalogued.

210
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:15,650
我们得先一步采取行动控制舆论
We need to get out ahead of it and control the story.

211
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:19,630
好吧  给我弄一份目前为止的调查报告
All right. Get me a copy and report on the investigation so far.

212
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,340
我想见他
I wanna see him.

213
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,700
总统
The president.

214
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:25,560
特勤局不许我进去
The Secret Service still won't let me.

215
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:29,230
请允许斯坦普先生见我丈夫
I'd like Mr. Stamper to have access to my husband, please.

216
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:30,990
我们有严格命令  夫人  只有您
We have strict orders, ma'am. Only you and--

217
00:15:30,990 --> 00:15:33,360
需要我亲自打给副总统吗
Would you like me to call the vice president myself?

218
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:36,220
道格拉斯  这位年轻人会送你进去
Douglas, this young man will escort you to his room.

219
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:37,260
谢谢
Thank you.

220
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:04,240
-几点了  -7点刚过
- What time is it? - It's a little past 7:00.

221
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,830
先生  先生  是道格
Sir? Sir, it's Doug.

222
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:17,230
虽然他睁开了眼
Just because his eyes are open 

223
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:19,090
但不代表他的意识完全清醒了
doesn't mean he's fully conscious.

224
00:17:19,090 --> 00:17:20,720
肝功能不足
Insufficient liver function.

225
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,810
他的大脑泡在一堆未处理的氨中
His brain is swimming in a pool of unprocessed ammonia.

226
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:26,870
如果他能看到什么  大概也是严重的幻觉
If he's seeing anything, it's probably severe hallucinations.

227
00:17:26,870 --> 00:17:28,600
他多久能得到肝脏
How long until he has a liver?

228
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:31,190
可能得要几小时  可能要几天
Could be hours. Could be days.

229
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,890
他是名单上第三位
He's number three on the list.

230
00:17:32,890 --> 00:17:33,580
第三名
Number three?

231
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:35,340
名单按序排序
It's prioritized in terms of need

232
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:37,270
他是1号情况的第一位
and who was listed first as a Status 1.

233
00:17:37,270 --> 00:17:39,360
他是美国总统啊
He's the President of the United States. 

234
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,680
这是法律
It's the law.

235
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:49,710
{\an7}纳·格林  我们知道是谁泄露了照片

236
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:51,630
{\an7}赛斯·格雷森

237
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:56,200
{\an8}道·斯坦普  我上车打给你

238
00:18:15,870 --> 00:18:17,770
司法部长要辞职
The attorney general is resigning.

239
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:21,080
把这条加入今天下午的新闻发布稿中
Add that to the press release for this afternoon.

240
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:25,540
-是她的决定还是副总统  -我的决定
- Uh, her decision or the vice president's? - My decision.

241
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:27,740
古德温的证人保护计划是司法部的责任
Goodwin's WITSEC was a DOJ responsibility.

242
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,160
我们得找个替罪羊
We needed a head to roll.

243
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,980
先是她  然后你
First hers... then yours.

244
00:18:35,390 --> 00:18:36,750
你明天辞职
You'll resign tomorrow.

245
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:46,930
道格  我知道你现在压力很大  但是
Doug, I know you're under a lot of pressure, but--

246
00:18:46,940 --> 00:18:49,990
是你发了那张南军士兵照片
You sent the photo of the rebel soldier.

247
00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:51,950
不是的
That's not true. 

248
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:54,910
私人手机  没在这里发
Personal phone, off the premises.

249
00:18:55,990 --> 00:18:57,710
可能是有人黑了我的账户什么的
You know, maybe somebody hacked my account or something--

250
00:18:57,710 --> 00:18:59,610
你真要再这么对我撒谎吗
Are you really gonna keep lying to me?

251
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,400
我可以叫人逮捕你
I could have you arrested.

252
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:04,610
但我宁可你低调离去
But I'd rather you go quietly.

253
00:19:10,820 --> 00:19:12,190
我知道些事  道格
I know things, Doug.

254
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:15,540
你证明不了什么
Nothing you can prove.

255
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:19,090
再威胁我啊
Now, threaten me again.

256
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,980
中国如果不加入  提议就不能成型
There's no proposal without China's involvement.

257
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:40,120
凯茜试了
Now, Cathy's tried,

258
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:43,380
但她跟他们的关系不是特别好
but she doesn't have the best relationship with them.

259
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:45,220
或许她需要帮助
Maybe she needs some help.

260
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:47,220
帮助  怎么说
Help? How?

261
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,670
你介意我抽烟吗
Do you mind if I smoke? 

262
00:19:52,670 --> 00:19:54,110
当然不
Of course not.

263
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,170
我十年前戒了
I quit about ten years ago.

264
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:04,260
玛乔莉逼我的
Marjory forced me to.

265
00:20:07,890 --> 00:20:11,400
还是那么好闻
Ah, still smells delicious.

266
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,290
玛乔莉死时什么样
What was it like when Marjory died?

267
00:20:20,770 --> 00:20:24,160
那是...
Oh, well, it was, um...

268
00:20:25,130 --> 00:20:27,370
抱歉  如果你不愿意我们不用谈这个
I'm sorry. We don't have to talk about it if you don't want.

269
00:20:27,370 --> 00:20:28,680
不  没事
No, it's fine.

270
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:32,620
我们当时已经数月没有真正聊过了
We hadn't had a real conversation in... in months.

271
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,990
她的神智已经不清楚了
Her mind was gone.

272
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,070
她最终死时
When she finally died, 

273
00:20:37,450 --> 00:20:41,230
感觉好像断了根肋骨
it felt like a limb had been hacked off.

274
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:44,720
我...痛不欲生
I felt... devastated.

275
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:49,760
但也如释重负
But I also felt relieved.

276
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:55,370
我对我母亲的感觉就是这样
That's what I feel about my mother.

277
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:59,050
我不...我都没想起来
Oh, I hadn't-- It hadn't even occurred to me.

278
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:01,010
除了弗兰克  你母亲也病了
You have Frank and your mother.

279
00:21:02,770 --> 00:21:04,360
父亲去世时  我几乎崩溃了
When my father died, it destroyed me,

280
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:07,780
但想到我母亲时  我毫无感觉
but when I think about Mother, I feel nothing.

281
00:21:08,050 --> 00:21:10,380
-你们不亲近吗  -不
- You two aren't close? - No.

282
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:16,950
我对弗兰西斯也是这种感觉
And I feel the same about Francis.

283
00:21:17,030 --> 00:21:18,170
毫无感觉
Nothing.

284
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,750
我知道这听起来很可怕
I know that must sound awful.

285
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,050
这很难接受
It's a lot to process.

286
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:32,340
这没有正误之分
There's no right way or wrong way.

287
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,450
-等下  慢着  -不
- Wait, hold on. - No.

288
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:41,710
玛乔莉不会同意的
Marjory wouldn't approve.

289
00:21:42,530 --> 00:21:44,260
刚刚说到哪了
We got sidetracked.

290
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:46,690
对  中国
Yes. China.

291
00:21:47,470 --> 00:21:51,150
我有个主意  如果你相信我能做好的话
I have an idea, if you can trust me to handle it.

292
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,320
我赌上命相信你  克莱尔
I'd trust you with my goddamn life, Claire.

293
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,800
你不会想知道的
You don't want to know.

294
00:22:12,210 --> 00:22:15,170
我来拿  谢谢
I got it. Ah, merci.

295
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,380
莉安
LeAnn.

296
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:35,200
找你可真难
You are a tough guy to track down.

297
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:38,370
-你来干什么  -你要赶飞机
- What are you doing here? - You have a plane to catch.

298
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:40,370
第一夫人需要你的帮助
The First Lady needs your help.

299
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,170
我不想和他们有任何瓜葛
I don't want to have anything to do with them.

300
00:22:42,170 --> 00:22:43,500
无论你对总统的看法如何
Whatever you think of the president,

301
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,410
你对祖国依然负有责任
you still have a duty to your country.

302
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:47,830
就算他在我离开白宫的那天去世
Even if he dies, the day I walked out the White House,

303
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:49,840
我也向自己承诺过不会回去
I promised myself I wasn't going back.

304
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,660
你连我们的计划都不知道
You don't even know what we have in mind.

305
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:54,640
无所谓  我不去
It doesn't matter. I'm not going.

306
00:22:54,830 --> 00:22:56,170
我想请你离开
I'd like you to leave.

307
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,870
这是基本情况的材料
Here's your briefing materials.

308
00:23:00,870 --> 00:23:01,710
你没听见我说吗
You're not hearing me.

309
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,270
你真应该看一眼
You should really take a look.

310
00:23:17,410 --> 00:23:19,360
她的竞选会完蛋的
Her campaign would be over.

311
00:23:21,810 --> 00:23:24,630
而且你父母会怎么想
And what would your parents think?

312
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:33,540
看上去就像你要利用他受伤...
It looks like you're taking advantage of the fact that he's--

313
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:35,020
康威仍在进行竞选活动
Conway is still campaigning.

314
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:36,080
他是共和党人
He's a Republican

315
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,600
而且他已经得到了提名
and he's already wrapped up his nomination.

316
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:38,480
和我们不一样
Apples and oranges.

317
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,270
如果我们什么都不做
We are gonna lose,

318
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:41,310
陪着一个不省人事的人干坐着  就会输
if we sit still, to a guy who's unconscious.

319
00:23:41,310 --> 00:23:44,460
希瑟说得对  安德伍德在大赚同情分
Heather's right. Underwood's scoring major sympathy points.

320
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:46,230
在接下来的七个州里  他在六个州领先
He's ahead in six of the next seven states.

321
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:47,550
我们得继续施压
We need to keep the pressure up.

322
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:49,150
俄国  油价
Russia, gas prices...

323
00:23:49,150 --> 00:23:51,510
攻击一位正与死神搏斗的总统
Attack a president who's fighting for his life?

324
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:53,620
叫你们来开会不是来辩论的
I didn't call this meeting to debate.

325
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:55,760
我要夺回那些州
I want those states back.

326
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:58,530
我们开始准备活动和媒体造势
So let's start organizing events and media hits.

327
00:23:58,530 --> 00:24:00,950
明早之前  确定初步预算和安排
Prelim budgets and schedules, by tomorrow morning.

328
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:04,980
对于古德温的动机  人们有多种猜测
There has been much speculation as to Goodwin's motivations.

329
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:06,990
辛西娅
Cynthia.

330
00:24:08,980 --> 00:24:10,580
古德温的事进展如何
Where are we on Goodwin?

331
00:24:11,050 --> 00:24:12,950
已经搞定了保安
The security guy's taken care of.

332
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:15,140
他没看见你们在一起
He never saw the two of you together.

333
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:17,930
那其他人呢
What about others?

334
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,930
据他所知  没有
None that he knows of.

335
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:22,310
但我们又不能四处询问
But it's not like we can ask around.

336
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:24,980
在2013年11月
In November of 2013,

337
00:24:24,990 --> 00:24:28,030
巴恩斯女士被华府地铁撞击身亡
Ms. Barnes was struck by a D.C. metrorail train.

338
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:29,450
{\an8}枪手确认是卢卡斯·古德温

339
00:24:28,130 --> 00:24:30,940
华府警方将其定性为一场事故
D.C. police classified it as an accident.

340
00:24:30,940 --> 00:24:32,140
有人推测...
Some have speculated that...

341
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,730
坐吧  雷米
Have a seat, Remy.

342
00:25:01,450 --> 00:25:02,840
弗兰克的事我很遗憾
Sorry about Frank.

343
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:04,630
拜托  省省吧
Oh, please, don't bother.

344
00:25:04,630 --> 00:25:06,290
我已经听够了人们说他们很遗憾
I've had enough people say they're sorry,

345
00:25:06,290 --> 00:25:08,150
我也知道你不是真心的
and I know you don't mean it.

346
00:25:08,740 --> 00:25:10,930
我没办法按你希望的那样帮你
I can't help you the way you want me to.

347
00:25:10,930 --> 00:25:13,030
莉安告诉我她已经跟你说得很明白了
LeAnn told me she was very clear with you.

348
00:25:13,030 --> 00:25:14,100
没用的
It won't work.

349
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:16,380
塔斯克比我更不想帮你
Tusk wants to help you even less than I do.

350
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:18,400
这不是谁在帮谁  雷米
Well, nobody's doing any favors here, Remy.

351
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,290
他会从中获得一大笔钱
He's going to get very rich from this.

352
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:21,730
你为什么不亲自跟他说
Why don't you speak to him yourself?

353
00:25:21,730 --> 00:25:23,490
因为他不会听我的
Because he won't listen to me.

354
00:25:23,550 --> 00:25:26,040
这必须听起来像是你的主意  而不是我的
This needs to seem like your idea, not mine.

355
00:25:26,340 --> 00:25:28,160
你也会捞上一大笔的
And you'll make a killing, too. 

356
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:29,660
我不需要钱
I don't need the money.

357
00:25:30,710 --> 00:25:33,120
因为你现在在乎的是别的
Because you care about other things now.

358
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,640
比如杰姬
Like Jackie.

359
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:39,350
所以你必须做成此事
Which is why you'll make this happen.

360
00:25:45,090 --> 00:25:47,170
如果我当初跟邓巴说了弗兰克的事
If I had told Dunbar about Frank...

361
00:25:48,210 --> 00:25:50,250
说他知道洗钱的事
about how he knew about the laundering,

362
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:53,760
他就当不了总统  我们现在也不会站在这儿
he wouldn't be president and we wouldn't be standing here.

363
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:56,420
但你没有  你现在也说不了了
But you didn't and you can't now, 

364
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,720
所以现在是这样
so here we are.

365
00:25:59,380 --> 00:26:01,900
两小时  我们毫无进展
Two hours and we got nowhere. 

366
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,570
他只想听中国的反映
All he wants to hear is China.

367
00:26:03,570 --> 00:26:05,470
我告诉他北京方面不回应
I told him Beijing is not responsive. 

368
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,670
他根本不在乎
He doesn't give a damn.

369
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,000
第一夫人给他提过醒了
The First Lady put a bug in his ear.

370
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,860
不管她说了什么  他铁了心不听我们的了
Well, whatever bug she put in there won't crawl out.

371
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,810
我会安排次会面  只有你我他三人
I'll set up a meeting. Just you, me and him.

372
00:26:12,810 --> 00:26:14,350
恐怕一次会面是不够的
I don't think a meeting is enough.

373
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:15,670
我们的副总统
We have a vice president

374
00:26:15,670 --> 00:26:18,130
不知道他在干什么  道格
that does not know what he is doing, Doug.

375
00:26:18,130 --> 00:26:19,950
他必须把外交事务
He needs to completely turn over

376
00:26:19,950 --> 00:26:22,010
全部转交给国务院
all diplomatic affairs to the State Department.

377
00:26:22,010 --> 00:26:24,160
-否则我完全无能为力  -现在不行
- Otherwise, my hands are tied. - Not now.

378
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:25,200
非常紧急
This can't wait.

379
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:27,520
我们结束后  我会去找你的
When we're finished, I will come and find you.

380
00:26:28,010 --> 00:26:30,050
您能让我们单独谈谈吗  国务卿女士
Could you give us a few moments, Madam Secretary?

381
00:26:30,050 --> 00:26:32,440
-赛斯  你太过分了  -没关系
- Seth, you're out of line! - It's all right.

382
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,150
给我打电话
Call me.

383
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:38,150
我会的  谢谢  凯茜
I will. Thank you, Cathy.

384
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:39,480
谢谢
Thank you.

385
00:26:41,610 --> 00:26:43,930
-你他妈在干什么  -你不能开除我
- What the fuck are you doing? - You can't fire me.

386
00:26:43,930 --> 00:26:46,320
你不能打断我和国务卿的会面
You don't interrupt a meeting with the Secretary of State.

387
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:48,340
我可以终结邓巴的竞选
I can end Dunbar's campaign. 

388
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,690
今天就结束掉
We can end it today.

389
00:26:50,390 --> 00:26:51,400
怎么做
How?

390
00:26:52,210 --> 00:26:54,330
如果我做到  你能让我留下吗
If I deliver, will you keep me on?

391
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,680
你得先告诉我
You tell me how first.

392
00:27:04,210 --> 00:27:05,540
坐吧  玛莎
Have a seat, Martha.

393
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,770
我重新考虑了一下你的辞职
I've had second thoughts about your resignation.

394
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:24,210
你还想继续当司法部长吗
Would you like to remain as attorney general?

395
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:27,110
是的  我想
Yes, I would.

396
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:28,770
谢谢  道格
Thank you, Doug.

397
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:31,270
希瑟·邓巴有没有告诉过你
Did Heather Dunbar inform you

398
00:27:31,270 --> 00:27:34,080
她和卢卡斯·古德温见过面
of a meeting between herself and Lucas Goodwin?

399
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:38,030
你要让我的下属审问我吗
You're having me interrogated by my own subordinates?

400
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:40,260
你能保住工作  他们才是你的属下
They only work for you if you keep your job.

401
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:42,840
我建议你回答他们的问题
I suggest you answer their questions.

402
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:44,650
我想要我的律师在场
I'd like a lawyer present. 

403
00:27:44,650 --> 00:27:46,190
我提醒你  女士
Let me remind you, ma'am.

404
00:27:46,190 --> 00:27:49,620
没告知我们已经构成了隐瞒证据
Failing to have informed us constitutes withholding of evidence.

405
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:51,760
希瑟是我的朋友
Heather is a friend.

406
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:53,220
非常简单  玛莎
It's very simple, Martha. 

407
00:27:53,220 --> 00:27:55,660
跟我们合作  你就继续当司法部长
You work with us, you stay on as AG.

408
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:57,560
不合作  我们就起诉
You don't, we prosecute.

409
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:06,790
女士们先生们  美国第一夫人
Ladies and Gentlemen, the First Lady of the United States.

410
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:10,530
大家下午好
Good afternoon, everyone.

411
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:13,400
我想向大家通报我丈夫康复的最新情况
I'd like to update you on my husband's recovery.

412
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,570
总统的医疗团队
The President's medical team 

413
00:28:15,570 --> 00:28:17,930
昨晚做出了全面的评估
gave me a full assessment last night

414
00:28:17,940 --> 00:28:19,770
他们最后的结论是
and they have come to the conclusion

415
00:28:19,770 --> 00:28:24,220
总统需要肝移植
that the President is in need of a liver transplant

416
00:28:24,220 --> 00:28:25,750
才能活下去
if he's to survive.

417
00:28:29,190 --> 00:28:33,470
我请求全国与我共同祈祷
I'm asking the nation to pray with me

418
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:36,950
弗朗西斯能尽快等到一个健康的肝脏
that a healthy liver makes its way to Francis soon.

419
00:28:39,220 --> 00:28:40,620
抱歉  请等一下
I'm sorry. A moment.

420
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,040
抱歉
I'm sorry.

421
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:46,060
她很厉害  对吧
She's good, isn't she?

422
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:49,520
你在这儿干什么
What're you doing here? 

423
00:28:49,530 --> 00:28:51,040
至于案件调查...
As for the investigation...

424
00:28:51,050 --> 00:28:52,540
第一夫人需要支持
First Lady wanted some support.

425
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:54,530
...联调局反恐处处长
...the FBI director of counterterrorism

426
00:28:54,530 --> 00:28:56,440
会向大家进行全面汇报  但是...
will give you a full briefing. But...

427
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:59,230
我认为有必要亲自澄清
I feel it's important to personally address

428
00:28:59,570 --> 00:29:02,560
在古德温先生住所找到的文件
the document found in Mr. Goodwin's residence

429
00:29:02,690 --> 00:29:06,330
本次发布会前刚刚发到大家手上
that was made available to you just before this conference.

430
00:29:06,330 --> 00:29:09,540
很多措辞足以成为引人注目的头条新闻
It's filled with language that would make for flashy headlines,

431
00:29:09,540 --> 00:29:13,130
比如谋杀  腐败
words like "murder," "corruption."

432
00:29:12,730 --> 00:29:15,540
{\an8}他杀害了佐伊·巴恩斯和彼得·罗素

433
00:29:13,140 --> 00:29:16,830
其中指控总统与彼得·罗素和
The accusation that the President was involved in the deaths

434
00:29:16,830 --> 00:29:19,580
佐伊·巴恩斯的死有关
of Peter Russo and Zoe Barnes.

435
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:29,030
{\an8}第一夫人发表全国讲话  古德温指安德伍德犯下谋杀

436
00:29:19,650 --> 00:29:22,020
还有"滥用职权"这样的字眼
Phrases like "abuse of power,"

437
00:29:23,170 --> 00:29:25,480
尽管这一切没有事实依据
while they have no basis in reality,

438
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:29,640
却让我们悲哀地一窥他饱受困扰的内心
they do give us a sad glimpse into a very troubled mind.

439
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:30,960
如果有人
And it pains me that anyone, 

440
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:34,500
即使是有精神疾病的人
even someone who is mentally ill,

441
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:36,470
真会相信古德温先生对我丈夫的指控
would think my husband is capable of

442
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:38,910
那会让我十分痛心
what Mr.Goodwin believed to be true.

443
00:29:39,910 --> 00:29:42,950
但最让我心痛的是古德温先生的父母
But mostly it pains me for Mr. Goodwin's parents,

444
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:45,190
他们还在应对失去儿子的痛苦
who are coping with the loss of their son.

445
00:29:45,370 --> 00:29:47,940
据大家说  他一生中大部分时候是个好人
And, by all accounts, he was a decent man for most of his life,

446
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:51,030
但显然  他内心的什么地方崩溃了
but clearly, something snapped in him

447
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:54,080
而他迫切需要的时候没能得到帮助
and he never got the help he so desperately needed.

448
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:57,210
所以我恳请大家尊重他的父母
So I ask that all of you respect his parents' grief

449
00:29:57,210 --> 00:30:01,050
不要对这个生病的年轻人的话加以渲染
by not sensationalizing the words of a sick young man.

450
00:30:01,470 --> 00:30:03,990
让我们记住劳伦斯和贝蒂·密查姆
And let's remember Lawrence and Betty Meechum,

451
00:30:03,990 --> 00:30:05,490
他们的儿子艾德华
whose son Edward 

452
00:30:05,690 --> 00:30:09,230
因为古德温先生的病献出了自己的生命
gave his life because of Mr. Goodwin's illness.

453
00:30:09,250 --> 00:30:13,080
艾德华的牺牲是我丈夫还活着的唯一原因
Edward's sacrifice is the only reason my husband is still alive.

454
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:14,400
我会永远感激
And I'll be forever grateful

455
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:17,260
他的友谊和奉献
for his friendship and his devoted service.

456
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:18,620
谢谢
Thank you.

457
00:30:23,020 --> 00:30:25,600
反恐处处长纳森·格林
Counterterrorism Director Nathan Green.

458
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:29,540
今天调查取得了新进展
Today we had a new development in the investigation.

459
00:30:30,230 --> 00:30:32,710
今天下午我们采访了司法部长
This afternoon, we interviewed the Attorney General.

460
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,450
她告诉了我们她和希瑟·邓巴
She gave us a full account of a conversation she had

461
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:38,300
在枪击当天进行的谈话的全部内容
with Heather Dunbar the day of the shooting.

462
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,410
谈话中  邓巴女士声称
In this conversation, Ms. Dunbar claimed to have met

463
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:43,570
曾亲自见过卢卡斯·古德温
with Lucas Goodwin personally.

464
00:30:43,820 --> 00:30:45,510
我们虽没有理由相信
And while we have no reason to believe

465
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:48,970
邓巴女士和刺杀企图有任何关系
Ms. Dunbar had anything to do with the assassination attempt...

466
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:53,500
我们会对她就这个宣称的谈话进行质询
we will be questioning her about this alleged conversation.

467
00:30:53,580 --> 00:30:54,700
你们要抓她吗
Are you arresting her?

468
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:56,510
不  女士  我们只是来问几个问题
No, ma'am. We're here to ask a few questions.

469
00:30:56,510 --> 00:30:58,330
-那你需要提交正式申请  -她现在在吗
- Then you need to make a formal request. - Is she here now?

470
00:30:58,330 --> 00:30:59,930
直接把申请发给我
Send the request directly to me,

471
00:30:59,930 --> 00:31:02,120
我会和邓巴女士的律师讨论
and then I'll discuss it with Ms. Dunbar's attorneys.

472
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,240
凯特
Hey, Kate.

473
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,630
我给你打过电话  固话和手机
I tried calling. Home and cell.

474
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,950
座机线拔了  手机关机了
Pulled out the cord. Turned off the cell.

475
00:31:14,990 --> 00:31:16,670
因为我这种人
Because of people like me.

476
00:31:17,020 --> 00:31:19,810
其他人至少有礼貌没跑来我家门口
The others had the courtesy not to show up on my doorstep.

477
00:31:19,810 --> 00:31:21,680
礼貌从没帮我达成什么目的
Courtesy never got me anywhere.

478
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:26,220
我们能谈谈吗  私下谈
Can we talk? Off the record.

479
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,700
要不是你的话...
If it were anyone but you... 

480
00:31:31,130 --> 00:31:32,680
幸运的是  是我
Well, luckily, it isn't.

481
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:37,100
我去牵福斯托  该遛他了
Let me get Fausto. It's time for his walk.

482
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:42,710
我是核行业的  不是化石燃料
I'm in the nuclear game, not fossil fuels.

483
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:45,460
没人有你在中国那样的关系
No one has the relationships you do in China.

484
00:31:47,020 --> 00:31:48,900
中国人已经跟我脱离关系了
Chinese disowned me.

485
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:50,730
他们会回心转意的
They'll come around.

486
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,330
谁让你来的
Who put you up to this?

487
00:31:55,740 --> 00:31:57,660
我要开自己的公司
Starting my own firm. 

488
00:31:57,950 --> 00:31:59,320
我以为你不干了
I thought you were out?

489
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:01,660
我那是在自欺欺人
I was fooling myself.

490
00:32:03,260 --> 00:32:05,680
总统刚被枪击
So, president gets shot,

491
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:09,790
你就忍不住要趁火打劫了
and you just can't help taking advantage of the chaos.

492
00:32:11,540 --> 00:32:14,260
你所说的火  我称之为机遇
What you call chaos, I call opportunity.

493
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,440
你是我的第一位客户
And you're my first client.

494
00:32:22,790 --> 00:32:24,560
祝你好运
I wish you the best.

495
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,970
但我不是你的第一位客户
But I'm not your first client.

496
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:31,140
我不想跟白宫扯上关系
I don't wanna have anything to do with the White House.

497
00:32:31,140 --> 00:32:33,510
你因为沃克的丑闻损失了很多钱
You lost a lot of money during the Walker scandal.

498
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:38,740
没错  正因此我才要拒绝你
I did, indeed, which is why I'm turning you down.

499
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:42,590
我很抱歉你跑了这么大老远结果被拒绝
I'm sorry you came all the way out here for a "No."

500
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:53,110
你不想进监狱吧
You don't wanna go to prison, do you?

501
00:32:55,090 --> 00:32:56,430
再失去仅剩的一切
Lose the rest of it?

502
00:32:56,430 --> 00:32:58,000
我已经被赦免了
I've already been pardoned.

503
00:33:00,290 --> 00:33:03,330
免的是洗钱罪  不是伪证罪
For the money laundering, not for perjury.

504
00:33:05,540 --> 00:33:06,980
你说沃克知道  但是他不知道
You said that Walker knew, and he didn't.

505
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:10,150
你没有说你当时是跟弗兰克合作
What you didn't say is that you were working with Frank.

506
00:33:12,890 --> 00:33:15,190
人家凭什么相信你而不是我
Why should anybody believe you more than me?

507
00:33:15,340 --> 00:33:16,830
你要么赌一把
You take that chance...

508
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:19,550
然后看着克雷顿-维斯特变成低价股
and watch Clayton West become a penny stock.

509
00:33:20,650 --> 00:33:23,990
要么我们成为终结石油危机的英雄
Or we're heroes for ending the oil crisis,

510
00:33:23,990 --> 00:33:26,890
大家都发财  你也能重树形象
everybody gets rich, your image is restored.

511
00:33:29,110 --> 00:33:30,500
他们也许还会让你选
They'll probably even let you choose 

512
00:33:30,500 --> 00:33:32,640
下一任驻北京的大使
the next ambassador in Beijing.

513
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,900
你不觉得那是真的吗
So you don't think any of it is true?

514
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,920
不
No.

515
00:33:43,570 --> 00:33:45,520
我想相信他
And I wanted to believe him.

516
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:49,410
那第一夫人泪眼汪汪说的那些话
So the First Lady's whole teary-eyed thing?

517
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:52,030
我觉得她是对的
I think she's right. 

518
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,990
卢卡斯是哪里崩溃了吧
Something in Lucas snapped.

519
00:33:54,930 --> 00:33:57,900
我认识的卢卡斯不会想杀死总统
I mean, the Lucas I knew wouldn't have tried to kill a president.

520
00:33:57,900 --> 00:34:00,430
没错  我就是这意思
Exactly. That's my point.

521
00:34:00,930 --> 00:34:04,520
你真觉得安德伍德杀过人吗
You honestly think Underwood was murdering people?

522
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:06,010
你的怀疑态度哪去了
Where is your skepticism?

523
00:34:06,010 --> 00:34:09,410
我怀疑卢卡斯  也怀疑白宫
I'm skeptical of Lucas and I'm skeptical of the White House.

524
00:34:09,420 --> 00:34:10,850
那怎么没证据
How come there's no proof? 

525
00:34:11,260 --> 00:34:12,430
没有
None.

526
00:34:12,580 --> 00:34:15,670
卢卡斯试了  我也试了
After Lucas tried, after I tried.

527
00:34:17,330 --> 00:34:18,960
我的建议是算了吧
My advice is to let it go.

528
00:34:19,740 --> 00:34:22,550
你只会重复我们的徒劳
You're gonna repeat the same goose chase we did.

529
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:24,670
我总得问一下
I had to ask.

530
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:28,800
-你的编辑说了什么  -说算了吧
- What does your editor say? - To let it go.

531
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,950
你看吧
You see?

532
00:34:30,270 --> 00:34:33,080
-他可不如你  -那是我以前
- He's not as good as you are. - Was.

533
00:34:34,180 --> 00:34:35,920
真希望你在《电讯报》工作
Wish you were at The Telegraph.

534
00:34:36,670 --> 00:34:38,540
是啊  要是有人被开了就告诉我
Yeah, let me know if anyone gets fired.

535
00:34:42,160 --> 00:34:45,190
{\an8}活体捐献者常见问题

536
00:34:47,370 --> 00:34:48,560
门没关
It's open.

537
00:34:55,170 --> 00:34:56,780
我一收到你的短信就尽快赶过来了
I came as soon as I got your text.

538
00:34:56,780 --> 00:34:58,660
发布会后我们忙得不可开交
We've been slammed since the press conference.

539
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:00,140
情况怎么样
How's it lookin'?

540
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:02,090
邓巴的事大受关注
Major play on the Dunbar story.

541
00:35:03,610 --> 00:35:05,930
让第一夫人去说是个好主意
It was a good idea to have the First Lady talk.

542
00:35:06,990 --> 00:35:08,110
你要喝苏打水吗
You want a soda?

543
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:09,670
来杯水什么的吗
A glass of water or anything?

544
00:35:11,010 --> 00:35:12,270
水就好
Water's fine.

545
00:35:21,750 --> 00:35:23,360
我已决定让你留下来了
I've decided you can stay.

546
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:26,830
道格  我希望你能理解
Doug, I hope you can understand.

547
00:35:28,080 --> 00:35:29,420
我紧张了
I got nervous.

548
00:35:29,870 --> 00:35:31,800
当时情况看起来不太好
You know, things weren't looking good and...

549
00:35:32,670 --> 00:35:35,540
我想留条退路  以防万一
yeah, I wanted an out, in case I needed one.

550
00:35:35,780 --> 00:35:37,630
那的确是个错误  我希望我没有那样做
I mean, it was a mistake. I wish I hadn't.

551
00:35:37,630 --> 00:35:38,850
你纠正了你的错误
You corrected your mistakes.

552
00:35:38,850 --> 00:35:41,000
那才是最重要的  要冰块吗
That's all that matters. You want ice?

553
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,080
好的
Sure.

554
00:35:51,500 --> 00:35:54,140
我们现在不能让竞选再出现问题了
We can't afford any more shake-ups in the campaign right now,

555
00:35:54,140 --> 00:35:56,020
尤其总统还在医院里
especially with the president in the hospital.

556
00:35:57,790 --> 00:36:00,070
我们也不能让你再犯错
We also can't afford any more of your mistakes.

557
00:36:04,210 --> 00:36:07,220
闭嘴  闭嘴
Shut up. Shut up!

558
00:36:07,990 --> 00:36:10,510
我刚醒来的时候  说不出话
When I first woke up, I couldn't speak.

559
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:12,450
我得眨眼来表达我的反应
I had to blink my eyes if I wanted to respond.

560
00:36:12,450 --> 00:36:13,670
你明白吗
Do you understand?

561
00:36:15,670 --> 00:36:17,890
如果我得不到你的忠诚
If I can't get your loyalty, 

562
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,530
那我就要你顺从
I will have your obedience.

563
00:36:20,830 --> 00:36:21,890
眨眼
Blink.

564
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:24,470
眨眼
Blink!

565
00:36:28,810 --> 00:36:29,840
该死
Fuck!

566
00:36:41,530 --> 00:36:42,460
该死的
Fucking...

567
00:36:50,010 --> 00:36:51,020
给
Here.

568
00:36:52,140 --> 00:36:53,580
你有病  伙计
You're fucked up, man.

569
00:37:12,820 --> 00:37:14,720
-别叫了  -早上好  汉默施密特先生
- Quit it. - Good morning, Mr. Hammerschmidt.

570
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:15,570
有什么事吗
How can I help you?

571
00:37:15,570 --> 00:37:17,030
我们来还你的笔记
Uh, we're just returning your notes.

572
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,480
我们复印过了  这是原件
We made copies. These are the originals.

573
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:20,870
不是很有用吧
Nothing too useful, huh?

574
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:23,090
是的  先生  但还是感谢你的配合
No, sir, but thank you for your cooperation.

575
00:37:23,090 --> 00:37:25,270
还有你的报纸  放在台阶上的
Your paper, too. It was on the step.

576
00:37:25,650 --> 00:37:26,970
祝你今天愉快  汉默施密特先生
Well, you have a good day, Mr. Hammerschmidt.

577
00:37:26,970 --> 00:37:28,080
你们也是
You, too.

578
00:37:35,980 --> 00:37:37,370
不要告诉我你又饿了
Don't tell me you're hungry already. 

579
00:37:37,370 --> 00:37:39,760
我才喂过你  天呐
I just fed you. Good God.

580
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:42,460
来了  来了  来了  来了
I'm coming. I'm coming, I'm coming, I'm coming.

581
00:37:43,180 --> 00:37:53,180
{\an8}未遂刺客说法被驳斥

582
00:37:58,850 --> 00:38:02,040
{\an8}邓巴未对古德温一事做出回应

583
00:38:18,390 --> 00:38:20,870
-早上好  -早上好
- Morning. - Morning.

584
00:38:27,190 --> 00:38:29,760
我建议让凯茜来做谈判
I suggest we turn the negotiations over to Cathy.

585
00:38:29,990 --> 00:38:31,940
如果我们一直拖着俄国  油价会
If we keep stalling on Russia, gas prices will--

586
00:38:31,950 --> 00:38:33,300
现在不是说这个的时候
Now is not a good time.

587
00:38:34,620 --> 00:38:35,430
我不会让总统
I won't have the president

588
00:38:35,430 --> 00:38:37,150
回到一个一片混乱的白宫
come back to a White House in disarray.

589
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:38,910
我们不知道他会不会回来
We don't know that he is coming back.

590
00:38:39,650 --> 00:38:42,850
他会的  我向你保证
He is. I promise you that.

591
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:46,660
你是上帝吗  你有什么资格保证
Are you God? Who are you to say?

592
00:38:47,890 --> 00:38:48,530
什么事
Yes?

593
00:38:48,530 --> 00:38:50,750
塔斯克先生和丹顿先生来了
Mr. Tusk and Mr. Danton are here. 

594
00:38:50,750 --> 00:38:51,870
让他们进来
Send them in.

595
00:38:52,010 --> 00:38:54,400
今早安排的  我们要讨论俄国的事
It was arranged this morning. We're discussing Russia.

596
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:55,980
先生  我是幕僚长
Sir, I am the Chief of Staff.

597
00:38:55,980 --> 00:38:57,750
这些事情你必须让我知道
You have to keep me informed of these things.

598
00:38:57,750 --> 00:38:58,780
不好意思
Excuse me,

599
00:38:58,780 --> 00:39:00,420
但我觉得应该是你要听我的
but I believe you answer to me, 

600
00:39:00,420 --> 00:39:01,670
而不是反过来
not the other way around.

601
00:39:01,670 --> 00:39:03,340
国务卿杜兰特应该参加这个会
Secretary Durant should be here.

602
00:39:03,340 --> 00:39:04,450
这是一次私下碰面
This meeting is private. 

603
00:39:04,450 --> 00:39:05,880
我之后会跟你们俩讨论
I'll discuss it with you both after.

604
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,760
总统绝不会允许雷蒙德
The president would never allow Raymond--

605
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:11,060
-总统先生  -塔斯克先生
- Mr. President. - Mr. Tusk.

606
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,500
雷米  很高兴见到你
Remy, good to see you.

607
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,670
-总统先生  -斯坦普先生
- Mr. President. - Mr. Stamper.

608
00:39:17,460 --> 00:39:19,270
我们稍后继续  道格
I'll follow up with you later, Doug.

609
00:39:19,330 --> 00:39:20,520
是  先生
Yes, sir.

610
00:39:21,700 --> 00:39:23,560
感谢您这么快就抽出时间见我们
Thanks for taking the time to meet with us on such short notice.

611
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:26,210
石油的问题没时间可以浪费了
Well, there's no time to waste on this oil thing.

612
00:39:26,330 --> 00:39:28,750
我跟中国那边有了些进展
I've made some progress with the Chinese.

613
00:39:29,170 --> 00:39:30,740
先生  第一夫人现在在里面
Sir, the First Lady is in there right now.

614
00:39:30,740 --> 00:39:32,210
她在等我
She's expecting me.

615
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:40,120
我们还想赢得选举呢
We're trying to win an election,

616
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,140
你却想提醒所有人
and you want to remind everyone

617
00:39:41,150 --> 00:39:43,170
总统赦免了雷蒙德·塔斯克
that the president pardoned Raymond Tusk?

618
00:39:43,170 --> 00:39:44,810
我们换个地方说
Let's find somewhere else.

619
00:39:44,810 --> 00:39:46,420
这都是国家大事
These are matters of state.

620
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:48,550
你无权干涉
You don't have the authority to intervene.

621
00:39:49,010 --> 00:39:51,450
如果唐纳德想听我的建议  那他就有权这么做
If Donald wants my counsel, that is his prerogative.

622
00:39:51,450 --> 00:39:53,030
你故意骗我
You are deliberately deceiving me.

623
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:56,040
-你背着我  -你忘了你的身份  道格拉斯
- Going behind my-- - You have forgotten your place, Douglas.

624
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:59,240
我的身份  那你呢
My place? What about your place?

625
00:39:59,590 --> 00:40:01,480
你在他最需要的时候离开  还威胁他
You leave him when he needs you most, you threaten him,

626
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:03,700
现在他进了医院  你还拆他的台
and now that he's in here, you undermine him.

627
00:40:03,700 --> 00:40:05,710
-你应该  -别说了  够了
- You're supposed to be-- - Stop. That is enough.

628
00:40:06,210 --> 00:40:07,890
我会告诉你一切
I will fill you in on everything,

629
00:40:07,890 --> 00:40:09,930
但不是在这儿  而是在白宫
but not here. At the White House.

630
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:13,630
怎么了
What's happening?

631
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:15,050
他的心脏
His heart.

632
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:19,360
-医生  -他有些偶发心律不齐
- Doctor? - He's had some sporadic arrhythmia.

633
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:21,590
-请出去一下好吗  -好
- Will you give us the room for a moment? - Of course.

634
00:40:28,220 --> 00:40:29,770
我们不能一直斗下去
We can't keep battling each other,

635
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:31,380
他都这样子了
not with him like this.

636
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:32,940
我们需要一条新的道路
We need a new path forward,

637
00:40:32,940 --> 00:40:34,850
我希望你能帮忙
and I would like your help with that.

638
00:40:34,990 --> 00:40:37,910
我保证不会瞒着你
I promise I won't keep you in the dark.

639
00:40:39,450 --> 00:40:41,930
等你准备好  我们白宫见
I'll meet you at the White House whenever you're ready.

640
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:45,700
我要留在这里  我觉得这更重要
I'm staying here. I think this is more important.

641
00:40:47,180 --> 00:40:48,280
好
Okay.

642
00:41:00,140 --> 00:41:01,320
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood.

643
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:04,990
关于如何对付俄国
Mr. Tusk and Mr. Danton have a proposal

644
00:41:04,990 --> 00:41:06,680
塔斯克先生和丹顿先生有个提议
about how to deal with Russia.

645
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:10,730
您今天最没想到会见到的就是我吧
I imagine I'm the last person you expected to see today.

646
00:41:11,850 --> 00:41:12,960
见到你们二位
I am a bit surprised,

647
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:15,050
我的确有些惊讶
yes, to see both of you.

648
00:41:15,530 --> 00:41:17,770
大家对我们的到来肯定都有些警觉
I'm sure there's some wariness about us being here,

649
00:41:17,770 --> 00:41:21,530
但我们有个对付俄国的好计划
but I think we have a good plan on how to handle Russia.

650
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,370
你想加入吗
Would you like to join us?

651
00:41:23,370 --> 00:41:25,300
让雷蒙德给你详说
Raymond can lay it out for you.

652
00:41:25,580 --> 00:41:27,770
我不知道我能提供些什么
Well, I don't know what I can offer.

653
00:41:28,130 --> 00:41:30,890
要是我又跟白宫打交道的消息传出去
Well, we're going to catch some flack if word gets out 

654
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:32,910
我们会受到抨击的
that I'm back in business with the White House.

655
00:41:32,910 --> 00:41:35,200
你可以帮我们平息那些声音
You could help us smooth that over.

656
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:38,820
你的新闻发布会相当感人
Your press conference was very moving.

657
00:41:40,540 --> 00:41:43,070
-弗兰克的事  我很遗憾  -谢谢
- I'm sorry about Frank. - Thank you.

658
00:41:43,350 --> 00:41:44,930
当然  他要是知道我进了总统办公室
Of course, he'd have a conniption fit

659
00:41:44,930 --> 00:41:47,460
肯定会大发脾气
if he knew I were in the Oval Office.

660
00:41:49,970 --> 00:41:52,800
他是个实用主义者  雷蒙德  只要成功就行
Well, he is a pragmatist, Raymond. Whatever works.

661
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:55,550
-我们继续吧  -雷米
- Shall we continue? - Remy.

662
00:41:55,900 --> 00:41:58,020
计划是向中美能源公司提出
So, the plan is to propose a partnership

663
00:41:58,020 --> 00:42:01,090
建立伙伴关系
between American and Chinese energy companies.

664
00:42:27,310 --> 00:42:29,300
你有点紧张
You seem nervous.

665
00:42:29,730 --> 00:42:30,960
有一阵子没见了
It's been a while.

666
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,680
我该怎么办  老大
What should I do, boss?

667
00:43:22,940 --> 00:43:23,870
萨克逊医生
Dr. Saxon.

668
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,220
我想捐肝
I'd like to donate.

669
00:43:32,020 --> 00:43:34,000
-斯坦普先生  -我是O型血
- Mr. Stamper-- - My blood type is O.

670
00:43:34,330 --> 00:43:36,220
我很健康  我们开始做测试吧
I'm healthy. Let's do the tests.

671
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:38,980
健康不是捐肝的唯一标准
That's not the only criteria for donation.

672
00:43:39,650 --> 00:43:41,550
你是个正在戒酒的酗酒者  我们不接受
You're a recovering alcoholic. We don't accept--

673
00:43:41,550 --> 00:43:43,280
我不管什么规则
I don't care about the rules.

674
00:43:43,450 --> 00:43:44,750
如果我配型成功  我希望你能做
If I'm a match, I want you to do it.

675
00:43:44,750 --> 00:43:46,630
就算成功了  也帮不上忙
Even if you were, it wouldn't matter.

676
00:43:47,430 --> 00:43:49,660
他已经病得太重  只有部分肝脏不够
He's too ill for a partial liver at this point.

677
00:43:49,660 --> 00:43:51,110
他需要一整个
He needs a full one.

678
00:43:52,020 --> 00:43:56,160
抱歉  但我们只能等待并企盼了
I'm sorry, but we'll just have to wait and hope.

